  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The objective of this trial is to guarantee a follow-up of all stroke and transient ischemic
      attack (TIA) patients. With this follow-up assessment long term effects of therapy and
      prevention measures can be detected and monitored. It is part of quality assurance.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Primary efficacy endpoint: Number of patients who state that they received all the
      information they want about the causes and nature of their illness Key secondary endpoint(s):
      Compliance/adherence with discharge medication. Re-events. Degree of Disability. Activities
      of daily living. Mortality.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
